Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil, season with
@salt and @pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Add the
@panko breadcrumbs{50%g} into another medium bowl and season with salt and
pepper.

Season the @British chicken thighs{3} with salt and pepper. Dip into the
bowl with egg and then into the bowl with the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's
completely coated.

Shake off the excess and transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil to coat the
bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay in the chicken and fry until golden-brown,
~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a baking tray, then bake on the middle shelf of your
oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Buffalo Inspired Hot Sauce ==

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pour in the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and
@water{50%ml}. Place the pan onto medium-high heat and bring to a boil.
Simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @sriracha sauce{15%g}, @chilli flakes{1%tsp} and
@honey{15%ml} until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Mix in the @butter{20%g} until melted, then transfer to a #small bowl{} and
set aside.

== Blue Cheese Slaw ==

Halve the @glazed burger buns{2}. When the chicken has ~{3%minutes} left,
pop the buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

In a #large bowl{}, add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and @soured cream{75%g}. Crumble
over the @crumbled blue cheese{30%g}, season with salt and pepper, then toss
to combine.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, pop the buns onto your plates.

Spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun bases, then top with the fried
chicken and drizzle over the buffalo inspired hot sauce. Close with the bun
lids.

Serve the chips and blue cheese slaw alongside.

Enjoy!